The paper deals with the problem of objective Quality-of-Experience (QoE) prediction for adaptive streaming videos, which involves analyzing the subjective characteristics of streaming videos and optimizing an objective QoE model. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Multimedia (cs.MM), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). Among these, cs.MM and cs.CV are the most likely categories, as they are directly related to multimedia and video processing. However, cs.IT, cs.NI, and cs.HC are also relevant, as they involve aspects such as information theory, networking, and human perception, which are important for QoE prediction.
